Fuji House of Commotion star, Sola Onayiga, has been confirmed dead. The veteran actress also known as Mrs. Oluwasolamipe Onayiga, who played the role of Ireti in Kunle Bantefa’s popular soap Fuji House of Commotion died few hours after her colleague, Ada Ameh’s demise. The actress who was popularly known for her comic role in the now rested show died at about 3.45am today July 18. Onayiga is also an accomplished Stage and Screen Actress and Fellow of Theatre Arts is best known for living delightfully the role of Ireti aka Cooking practicals in the defunct television sitcom. Her family members are yet to release an official statement on the details surrounding her death.